##The latest outbreak: 440 cases confirmed nationwide, three places appear human-to-human transmission of "second generation cases"

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

* As of 24:00 on January 21, a total of 440 new pneumonia cases had been reported in 13 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) .
* Experts believe that since January 18, the rapid increase in the number of confirmed cases, there are "first-generation cases" to "second-generation cases" factors.
* Epidemic situation of times coronavirus pneumonia spreads, can be clear is 2 generation case, had had Guangdong, Wuhan, Shanghai 3 place to report so far.
* The National Health Commission and the State Medical Insurance Bureau have taken corresponding measures to deal with the epidemic.
* To prevent the spread of the epidemic, Wuhan started strict control of people entering and leaving.
* The Hubei provincial government announced in the early hours of May 22 that it had launched a second-level emergency response to public health emergencies.

As of 24:00 on January 21, a total of 440 confirmed cases of new pneumonia had been reported in 13 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) .

Experts believe that since January 18, the rapid increase in confirmed cases, there is the epidemic from "one-generation cases" to "two-generation cases" factors.

The transmission of coronavirus pneumonia, can be identified as the second-generation cases, so far there have been Guangdong, Wuhan, Shanghai three notification.

The National Health Commission and the State Medical Insurance Bureau have taken corresponding measures to deal with the epidemic situation.

In order to prevent the spread of the epidemic, Wuhan has started strict control over the entry and exit of people.

In the early hours of January 22, the Hubei provincial government announced the launch of a secondary emergency response to public health emergencies.

At 10 a.m. on January 22, the State Council Information Office held a press conference to announce the latest outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia:

As of 2400 hours on January 21, the COVID-19 had received 440 confirmed cases of pneumonia, 9 deaths and 3 new cases from 13 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities, all of which were in Hubei Province. Among them, on January 21(0-24 hours) , 149 cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia with coronavirus infection were reported (see the end of this article for detailed data) .

It has been more than 20 days since the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission first reported cases of pneumonia on December 31,2019. During this period, the turning point occurred after January 18,2020, as the number of confirmed cases increased rapidly from 41 to 440, and from Wuhan to 13 provinces.

Since January 18, there has been a dramatic increase in the number and location of confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia, which has triggered social tensions. The immediate question for the public is why the number of cases has increased so rapidly in just three or four days?

Some epidemic experts believe that since January 18, the rapid increase in confirmed cases, both the speed of virus diagnosis, epidemic notification mechanism changes, but also the epidemic from "one-generation cases" to "two-generation cases" factors.

Second-generation cases, in short, are cases of human-to-human transmission. How to prevent and control the second-generation cases is the focus of the current epidemic prevention and control.

Official notification of outbreak phase 1

The official case notification of the outbreak has gone through three stages.

The first phase, from December 31,2019, to January 5,2020, was notified by the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission.

The first notification of the first phase was made at 13:00 p.m. on December 31,2019, when the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission revealed that "27 cases (pneumonia) have been detected so far. ".

The last notification of the first phase was made at 8 pm on January 5,2020, when the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission revealed that as of 8 pm on January 5, the city had reported "59 patients with viral pneumonia diagnoses of unknown causes. ".

In the first phase of the officially reported outbreak, the cause of the pneumonia has not been identified and is therefore referred to as the "viral pneumonia of unknown origin" . Both cases occurred in Wuhan.

Official notification of outbreak Phase II

The second phase of the officially notified outbreak occurred between January 11 and January 18. The reporter is Wuhan City Health Committee.

Between January 5 and January 11, no cases were reported by the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission. But in the meantime, the country's authorities have identified the outbreak as COVID-19 pneumonia.

The first notification of the second phase was at 7:00 a.m. on January 11, when the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission announced that as of 24:00 a.m. on January 10,41 confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia had been reported in the city. The notification also said no new cases had been detected since January 3.

Since then, January 12,13,14,15,16, Wuhan City Health Commission daily case notification. Each notification indicates that no new confirmed cases were reported in the city between 0 and 24 hours of the previous day.

As a result, the second phase of the official epidemic case report, presented three characteristics: First, the previous unexplained pneumonia identified as COVID-19 pneumonia; second, this phase no new cases, the number of confirmed cases remained at 41; Third, all cases are in Wuhan, the field has not been reported cases.

Official notification of outbreak Phase III

The third phase of officially notified cases began at 12:10 a.m. on January 18, when the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission reported four new confirmed cases on January 16. This is the first new confirmed case in Wuhan since January 3.

At 12:43 am on January 19, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission reported that 17 new cases were confirmed on January 17.

January 20 at 2:42 am, Wuhan City Health Commission reported, January 18-january 19 two days, a total of 136 new confirmed cases.

At 2:44 a.m. on January 20, the Beijing Daxing District Health and Health Commission reported that two cases had been confirmed in the district.

A few minutes later, at 2:51 a.m. on January 20, the Guangdong Provincial Health and Health Commission reported that one case had been confirmed in the province.

On the evening of January 20, the Shanghai Municipal Health and Health Commission reported the first confirmed case in the city.

On January 21, the National Health Commission began compiling and reporting the number of confirmed cases nationwide: As of 2400 hours on January 20, a total of 291 cases (270 in Hubei Province, 5 in Beijing, 14 in Guangdong Province and 2 in Shanghai) were reported.

As of 10:00 am on 22 January, the third phase of the official notification of the State Council Information Office had two characteristics: First, the number of confirmed cases had increased rapidly from 41 at the end of the second phase, the number of cases increased rapidly to 440(data was reported at 10:00 am on January 22) . Secondly, the number of cases spread from Wuhan to 13 provinces.

"second-generation cases" of human-to-human transmission have emerged

Thus, nearly 90% of the confirmed cases of coronavirus pneumonia occurred in the third phase of officially notified cases, and far exceeded the number in Wuhan.

Why?

One of these is the speed of virus detection: Around mid-january, the use of new virus detection kits, the speed of virus detection accelerated, from the original one to two weeks, shortened to two to three days.

Second, the local reporting mechanism has been adjusted: Before January 20, all localities are waiting for the National Health Commission to confirm the diagnosis before reporting to the public. After January 20, local authorities began to self-confirm and self-publish cases according to the "National Health Commission General Office's plan for issuing pneumonia diagnosis and treatment for COVID-19 infection (trial version 2) " , and the rate of disclosure of cases accelerated.

But before this, each place initially reports the confirmed case, the time of onset mostly in early January, the time of diagnosis needs more than ten days. For example, the first case of coronavirus-infected pneumonia reported in Guangdong Province was visited by family members in Wuhan on 29 December 2019; became ill on 3 January 2020; returned to Shenzhen on 4 January; was transferred to a hospital for isolation on 11 January; was diagnosed on 19 January; Bulletin of 20 January.

Experts believe that this is because of the new test standards and reagents out before the process caused by the problem. First, hospitals around the suspected cases, to report to the local CDC. After the local CDC testing, samples will be sent to the National CDC, the National CDC review, the case can be confirmed.

In addition to the above two reasons, at present, what worries experts most is that the recent phase of the rapid increase in confirmed cases, indicating that there are now obvious "second-generation cases" appear.

The so-called second-generation cases, refers to the virus from the source of infection (in this case, the source of infection in the south China seafood market, the source of infection may be wild animals) directly transmitted to people (this is a case of one generation) , and then infected by a case of one generation, continue to infect new infections (second-generation cases) through human-to-human transmission.

The transmission of coronavirus pneumonia, which may involve second-generation cases, has so far been reported in three places:

Guangdong was the earliest.

The Guangdong Provincial Health Commission announced at 20:00 on the evening of January 20 that the expert group of Guangdong Province, in accordance with "the General Office of the National Health Commission on the printing and distribution of the COVID-19 pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan (trial version 2) , " A total of 13 new cases were confirmed, of which "11 cases had a history of residence or travel in Wuhan, and 2 cases had a history of close contact with the case" . These 2 cases "have a history of close contact with the case" , that is, may be the second generation of human-to-human cases.

According to media reports, one of Guangdong's human to human cases occurred in Zhuhai: A parent visiting from Wuhan passed the virus to her daughter in Zhuhai.

Next is Wuhan.

At 1:45 am on January 21, Wuhan Health Officials announced that 15 medical staff members had been diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia.

On the evening of January 21, Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang further revealed in an interview with CCTV that Wuhan medical staff had contracted COVID-19 pneumonia, which occurred at the Wuhan Union Hospital. The source of infection was a patient in the Department of neurosurgery of the hospital, during which a doctor and 13 nurses were infected.

COVID-19, which is passed from patient to health care worker during patient surgery, is also a second generation case of human to human transmission.

Then Shanghai.

As of 19:00 pm, there were four new confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Shanghai, the city's health and Health Commission said Tuesday. Among them, 3 cases had a history of residence or travel in Wuhan, and 1 case was found from close contacts.

This 1 case, "found from close contacts" , also indicates a second-generation case of human-to-human transmission.

Ceng Guang, a member of the high-level Expert Group of the National Health Commission, believes that the emergence of second-generation cases is a clear signal of the spread of the epidemic. But there is no conclusive evidence that the virus has mutated. If the virus mutates, the most serious consequence is that it is better adapted to spread from person to person, causing more infections.

Another expert, who spoke on the condition of anonymity, said the CDC had only detected the initial cases, and that the virus in those cases had not mutated. It is now imperative to sequence the genomes of subsequent cases to determine whether the virus has mutated.

The experts believe that after the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan was closed on January 1,2020, there would be no possibility of infection by visiting the market. Including the incubation period of this coronavirus, we can roughly infer that the cases infected after January 10, basically can be identified as second-generation cases, that is, human-to-human cases.

In another alarming sign, Chinese Academy of Engineering Academician Zhong Nanshan, the head of the National Health Commission's High Level Expert Group, not only mentioned in a media interview that the virus has the ability to pass from person to person, his biggest fear is that the next "super spreader" will emerge.

The so-called super-disseminator, is refers to has the extremely strong virus to infect others the patient. On January 21st the Mayor of Wuhan revealed that 14 medical staff had been infected by the same patient in a Wuhan Union Hospital outbreak. This patient may be the "super spreader. ".

Zeng thinks this suggests human-to-human transmission, but not that each case is contagious. "It could be a mutation, or it could be something else, like the virus spreading to a densely populated area, meeting a vulnerable group, or being in a closed environment. "

There are no second-generation cases in the initial quarantined population

The timing of our intervention and attention to COVID-19 is different from the SARS epidemic in 2003, Zeng said. When the intervention of SARS in, the time has been relatively late, so the evolution of SARS is relatively complete. Now the new coronavirus, can only be observed in the early stages, so there will be a process, both epidemiologically and clinically.

On December 8,2019, the first case of pneumonia of unknown cause appeared in Wuhan. At the end of December, as the number of cases increased, Wuhan's disease control authorities became aware of the outbreak and sent samples to the National CDC. On January 1,2020, with the genetic sequence of the virus still unknown, Wuhan moved quickly to shut down and disinfect the south China Seafood Market, the source of the infection. On the other hand, hundreds of close contacts of patients were isolated and controlled.

The above-mentioned experts said that the week before the closure of the south China Seafood Market should be the most infectious period of the virus, and with the incubation period of about one week for the virus, cases that occurred before January 10,2020, should be counted as a generation of cases, that is, these patients were infected by direct exposure to the south China seafood market, not by others.

Zeng said there were no second-generation cases among the hundreds of people initially quarantined. This virus early toxicity is not strong, the ability of human-to-human transmission is relatively poor. The initial infection was environmental exposure.

Clinicians involved in the treatment also mentioned that the initial patient's condition was not particularly severe and the fever was not particularly high, which also means that the virus is weak and consistent with epidemiological observations.

Joint Prevention and control, measures to upgrade

Recently, the National Health Commission led the establishment of the joint prevention and control mechanism for COVID-19 pneumonia, and also dispatched state-level medical experts to Wuhan to guide the medical treatment work, and implemented a "one-person-one-case" policy for severe cases, do Your best to reduce severe illness and death.

On January 21, the State Medical Insurance Bureau decided to adopt a special reimbursement policy for patients diagnosed with "COVID-19 pneumonia. ".

First, all the drugs and medical service items covered by the COVID-19's pneumonia diagnosis and treatment program will be temporarily brought into the coverage of the Medical Insurance Fund.

Second, to ensure the timely payment of patients'expenses, especially to play the role of Insurance of medical assistance funds, to eliminate patients'medical concerns. For patients in different places, treatment first and settlement later, reimbursement will not be carried out to reduce the proportion of transfer payment regulations, reduce the risk of infection caused by patient flow.

Third, for centralized hospitals, the Medical Insurance Department will advance funds to reduce the pressure of hospital advance payment, and patients'medical expenses will no longer be included in the total hospital budget control targets.

On the evening of January 21, the Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China said that Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China, National Railway Administration, Civil Aviation Administration of China and the China National Railway Corporation had decided that passengers who choose to travel by rail, road, water, civil aviation, etc. , exemption of its arrival and departure from Wuhan train tickets, bus tickets, ship tickets, tickets refund handling fees.

In the early morning of January 22, the Hubei Provincial Government issued a notice on strengthening the prevention and control of pneumonia in COVID-19: In order to strengthen the prevention and control of pneumonia in Covid-19, and effectively prevent the spread of pneumonia in COVID-19, decided to initiate a secondary response to a public health emergency.
